    "rationale": "This plan is built for an optimization problem: 80% India equity (large+mid+small) + 12% US large-cap + 8% gold, all at near-minimum cost. For a ₹34y, 18y horizon investor with 30% tax bracket and aggressive risk appetite, this captures the maximum expected return (12-14% pre-tax) while keeping fees below 0.25% average. The 65% equity rule means all funds are equity-taxed (12.5% LTCG), saving vs slab tax. US exposure (12%) is speculative-growth-heavy (S&P 500) but essential for global diversification. Gold (8%) is slab-taxed but acts as a portfolio stabilizer. No debt solely due to 18y horizon, but we'll add it if any liabilities emerge.",
